snippet.textDisplay: I strongly agree that we should use careful intention with our money. I am confused about how you avoided the most important reason to avoid counterfeit products; the fact that they financially support organized crime all over the world and therefore literally fund violence. Of course creators of products and consumers also suffer, but the bigger deal is really the life-threatening suffering it causes in the communities where these products come from all over the world. I respectfully encourage you to dive deeper into the subject you touched on around Amazon; your suspicions about their countless supply chains are well-founded. If you want to vote with your substantial dollars, I really hope you consider how shopping with smaller companies could make an impact on people all over the world. Much love!
